- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper is about natural language understanding and semantic parsing. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a new framework for integrating neural networks with non-differentiable memory to support symbolic reasoning. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of deep neural networks and reinforcement learning for training the proposed framework. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is relevant as the paper proposes a neural network architecture for the framework. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper introduces a new software framework for natural language understanding and symbolic reasoning.
